                                                                                                                                  Business Briefs

               
	 Mumbai, Jan. 22: The board meetings of the associate banks of the State Bank of India (SBI) scheduled for Thursday have been called off by SBI chairman O.P. Bhatt, one of the bank unions claimed today. However, the unions of the six associate banks will go ahead with their strike on January 25 and February 25 and 26, said G.D. Nadaf, general secretary of the All India State Bank Officers Federation. 
              
	 Bangalore, Jan. 22: Infosys Technologies has imposed a fine on its ceo and managing director, S. Gopalakrishnan, for not reporting within the stipulated time a change in his shareholding. On December 24 last year, Gopalakrishnan inherited 12,800 equity shares from his mother.
              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 22: The RBI will announce its third quarterly review of the monetary policy on January 29. RBI governor Y.V. Reddy has said the risk of a US recession will be dealt with in the review
              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 22: Grasim Industries has posted a 29.06 per cent increase in consolidated net profit at Rs 721.86 crore for the quarter ended December 31, 2007 compared with Rs 559.31 crore in the year-ago period. 
              
	 Calcutta, Jan. 22: Balmer Lawrie amp; Co has recorded a 9 per cent rise in total income for the third quarter ended December 31 at Rs 350 crore against Rs 321 crore in the year-ago period.
                                                            
